@jarondl I agree that `tz.gettz()` should be the proper way to get a time zone for sure, though presumably some people will prefer to use dateutil's zoneinfo, so I can see the utility in having the `zoneinfo.gettz()` module function.

I kinda think that this is something that can be solved by being explicit in the documentation so that projects like `pandas` can understand the clear difference between `zoneinfo.gettz()` and `tz.gettz()`.

I don't see this as being so useless that the feature should be dropped entirely, as long as we're clear that it's purely a convenience function, and that if they want to avoid whatever problems that might come up like caching of zoneinfo files, they should instantiate their own ZoneInfoFile object.

